{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-01437/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-01437"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:14:37"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man wearing glasses smiles at a waitress's notepad while she takes his order."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-01437","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-01437"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1/317084d1-0097-4d9f-a5bb-375bf04427d9","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:30:50.579Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds demands that Alma “show [him]” the order slip. He is used to giving orders and receiving exactly what he wants from the women in his life.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:743.7810218978102,106.66423357664232,536.3102189781023,584.014598540146"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1/6063b666-1028-4640-91ae-536ed89c0af7","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:31:08.445Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma answers affirmatively that she’ll remember Reynolds’s extravagant order. There’s more to her answer, however. First, it asserts her confidence in their relationship; she’ll be able to stand up to Reynolds when the time comes. Second, this proclamation brings to mind some of her final lines in the film: “Sometimes I jump ahead in our life together, and I see a time near the end. I can predict the future, and everything is settled. And all our lovers and children and friends come back and are welcome. And we have large gatherings where everyone is laughing and playing games. I am older and I see things differently, and I finally understand you. I take care of your dresses, keeping them from dust and ghosts and time.” Her power in the relationship, then, is rooted in her ability to remember, to define how their story is told, and, consequently, to figuratively take control over time. She is the one, after all, who will recount to Dr. Hardy their story in the film’s framing scenes.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:22.248175182481802,45.864963503649676,298.18248175182475,190.14963503649625"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1/ce638dc1-f299-460f-bf97-88b02c5c9876","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:31:21.443Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The battle for control in Reynolds and Alma’s relationship begins in this scene. Along with their exchanges about food and remembering, Reynolds declares that he’ll keep the paper on which Alma wrote his order. It’s the first in a series of power moves between the two.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01437/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:269.0912408759124,648.4598540145985,429.3941605839417,263.8248175182483"}}}]}]}]}